  "label": "Bafflelit Sleep Alcove",
  "description": "Bafflelit Sleep Alcove constitutes a narrow sleeping chamber cut from dark basalt masonry, its edges sealed with salt-cement joints that resist Brineshade’s measured tidal stresses. A fixed bunk platform and recessed storage niches occupy the thicker interior wall, minimizing exposure to the terminator’s temperature swing. A slit vent feeds through grit filters into a small flue stack, maintaining dry circulation against mineral haze intrusion. Light enters only through a shuttered baffle grille, holding the room in a deliberate, even dimness beneath Saltharrow’s hard white radiance.",
